n* Armindo Neves (1993)\n|colwidth=\n22em\n}}\n\n==Comedy==\nIn the late 1990s the English actor and comedian [[Steve Coogan]] created the character ''\"Tony Ferrino\"'' for his television comedy series. ''\"Tony Ferrino\"'' is supposedly a Portuguese singer and winner of the Eurovision Song Contest; he is a stereotype based on singers and entertainers often seen on European television programmes in the 1970s and 1980s. The [[BBC]] produced a one-off programme ''The Tony Ferrino Phenomenon'' in 1997.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 1965 - Simone de Oliveira.jpg|[[Simone de Oliveira]] in Naples ({{Escyr|1965}})\nFile:JoseCidEurovision.jpg|[[Jos\u00e9 Cid]] in The Hague ({{Escyr|1980}})\nFile:Sofia Vit\u00f3ria - Portugal 2004.jpg|[[Sofia Vit\u00f3ria]] in Istanbul ({{Escyr|2004}})\nFile:ESC 2007 Portugal - Sabrina - Dan\u00e7a comigo.jpg|[[Sabrina (Portuguese artist)|Sabrina]] in Helsinki ({{Escyr|2007}})\nFile:V\u00e2nia Fernandes Final.jpg|[[V\u00e2nia Fernandes]] in Belgrade ({{Escyr|2008}})\nImage:Esc port.jpg|[[Flor-de-Lis]] in Moscow ({{Escyr|2009}})\nFile:Filipa Azevedo 01.JPG|[[Filipa Azevedo]] in Oslo ({{Escyr|2010}})\nFile:ESC2014 - Portugal 01.jpg|[[Suzy (singer)|Suzy]] in Copenhagen ({{Escyr|2014}})\nFile:20150520 ESC 2015 Leonor Andrade 3452.jpg|[[Leonor Andrade]] in Vienna ({{Escyr|2015}})\nImage:Salvador Sobral (Eurovision 2017).jpg|[[Salvador Sobral]] in Kyiv ({{Escyr|2017}})\nImage:Cl\u00e1udia Pascoal (Portugal 2018).jpg|[[Cl\u00e1udia Pascoal]] in Lisbon ({{Escyr|2018}})\nImage:ESC2019-Portugal.jpg|[[Conan Os\u00edris]] in Tel Aviv ({{Escyr|2019}})\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Portugal in the Junior Eurovision Song Contest]] &ndash; Junior version of the Eurovision Song Contest.\n*[[Portugal in the Eurovision Dance Contest]] &ndash; Dance version of the Eurovision Song Contest.\n*[[Portugal in the Eurovision Young Dancers]] &ndash; A competition organised by the EBU for younger dancers aged between 16 and